editorialSummary.text: Namesake chain highlighting the designer's chic, upscale women's clothing, shoes & accessories.

originalText.text: Shout out to Tory Burch in Hudson yards. Michelle you made my day. I Walked in right before closing time on Mother’s Day Sunday. I was expecting to be rushed but Michelle took her time and took care of me even after the store was closing up she made sure I had what I needed. Made my Mother’s Day complete. This will be the only Tory Burch store I will be visiting from now on. If you see Michelle tell her I sent you ! Thank you again .

originalText.text: I am very very disappointed because I was trying to shop at this store and buy a gift for my daughter. I asked the young lady, Giselle for some help and she waved me off. Then i asked again and she said just wait can’t you see I’m busy. I said ok, and then she waved me off. I walked out. Went to shop at Nordstrom instead.

originalText.text: If anyone shops here ask for Nicole. She’s very professional and is aware of her job function. When I went to the store Nicole made it very comfortable to be there and also was willing to work with anyone that has any questions regarding the appropriate gift to buy. Thanks Nicole !!

originalText.text:
Not very impressed with the employees. Four women were falling all over themselves to help me. I will say they were helpful. I just was really turned off which is too bad. I made a nice purchase. Another great thing was they shipped the items home for me. I was in NYC visiting. It was nice not to haul my purchases around the city all day or drag them through the airport. The thank-you email I got was very impersonable. Oops! Someone wasn't paying attention to detail.

It was such a pleasure to meet you today. I hope you love the [item purchased]. I think it's just perfect for [event, occasion, trip]. Please don't hesitate to contact me if I can assist you in any other way or if you'd like to schedule a personal styling appointment.

Thank you for shopping at Tory Burch.

originalText.text:
Customer service was great. I needed some retail therapy and the staff was very nice.
Unfortunately the same cannot be said about the quality of the product. I don't know how I did not realize it, was it the lighting? I don't know. I don't think the shoes was made of leather at all. I wore them at home twice to break them in before wearing them outside. They felt like rocks, the frame does not allow for much movement at all. They hurt my feet like crazy even after the third time wearing them. I think they were probably mold out of plastic. I was very disappointed, I don't think I'll buy anything from Tory Burch again.
